proxmox-datacenter-manager-ui (1.1.1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * views: map widget: keep an open info card aligned with its marker while
    the page scrolls, and use an info icon rather than a question-mark one for
    the node-list tooltip.

  * auto-installer:
    - expose the advanced filesystem options, such as the ZFS and Btrfs
      settings, in the create wizard, not only when editing an existing
      answer; the Advanced toggle now appears automatically on steps that
      contain advanced fields
    - fix template counters: a counter no longer snaps to zero on its first
      edit, a form reset restores the seeded value, and counters are
      constrained to non-negative values; more generally, deleting a row in a
      key-value list no longer copies its value onto the next row
    - improve the authorization-token edit dialog: gate Update on an actual
      change and offer Reset, fix clearing and partial entry of the expiry,
      and show its year, date, and time correctly
    - prefill the preparation command with the host's TLS fingerprint and the
      Datacenter Manager's own origin, taking both from the entered answer
      when creating one
    - refresh the token panel after an answer auto-creates its token, re-sync
      the token selector on reset, and align the Network and Disk tabs

  * confirm dialogs: stop styling routine confirmations as errors; a
    confirmation now uses a neutral question icon and focuses the affirmative
    button, reserving the alerting icon and safe-button focus for genuinely
    destructive actions like removing a remote, deleting a certificate, or
    rebooting a node.

  * guest snapshots: title the dialog with the guest name and source remote
    (a bare VMID is ambiguous across remotes), and tune the dialog size and
    actions column.

  * lxc/qemu: drop the deprecated HA group information, superseded by HA
    node-affinity rules since Proxmox VE 9.0.

  * guests: improve the empty-list placeholder contrast, which was hard to
    read in dark mode.

  * subscription registry: clarify some tooltips, e.g., quote the referenced
    button names.

  * administration: rename the system log tab to "System Log" to follow suite
    with Proxmox VE and other products, that changed to the more generic term
    already since a while.

