proxmox-datacenter-manager-ui (1.0.7) trixie; urgency=medium

  * map widget: actually plot remote locations on the world map. The
    pwt-assets submodule needed an update for the leaflet map classes, and the
    per-node location data needed a force reload so it surfaces after the
    cache is refreshed.

  * pve: snapshots: close the description-edit dialog on a successful update;
    previously the dialog stayed open even though the change had already been
    applied in the background.

  * ceph: rephrase the OSD column from "{up} / {in} / {total}" to "{up} up,
    {in}/{total} in" to make the two independent dimensions (running vs.
    participating in data placement) readable as one cell.

  * ceph: pools: allow sorting by Used % so operators can quickly spot the
    most- and least-utilized pools when triaging capacity.

  * ceph: allow row selection in the cluster panels (CephFS, flags, managers +
    MDS, monitors, OSDs, pools) for orientation and screenshots; the selection
    is purely visual, no action fires on select.

  * ceph: open the matching PVE Ceph subview from the "Open Web UI" button
    instead of always landing on the top-level Ceph node tab. The mapping
    covers Monitors, OSDs, Pools, CephFS and Flags (which PVE manages from the
    OSD panel).

  * ceph: fix the vertical alignment of the per-OSD usage meter.

  * auto-installer: prepared-answer form polish:
    - include the certificate fingerprint in the suggested
      proxmox-auto-install-assistant prepare-iso command line so it can be
      copied and run as-is; ship a default template that users can adapt
    - refresh the advanced filesystem options in place when the filesystem
      field changes; previously only a Save + re-open round-trip would surface
      the matching options
    - require a non-empty disk-filter and network-filter list so an empty
      list is rejected up-front rather than later by the apply step ("need
      either disk-list or filter set"); also fix the network filter's disabled
      gate to key off the DHCP network checkbox instead of the unrelated DHCP
      FQDN one
    - validate the template-counter name field properly, allow new counters
      to be added, parse an empty counter default value as 0, and make the
      FQDN field a large field with an empty default
    - filter the country and keyboard-layout dropdowns by both ISO code and
      full name so users can search by either, and auto-select the matching
      entry as they type
    - stop silently dropping the advanced ZFS ARC max size and the ZFS and
      Btrfs compression algorithm when saving a prepared answer
    - allow saving a prepared answer that takes its FQDN from DHCP, which
      previously failed with a "missing field" error

  * auto-installer: drop URL encoding from the token ID during creation so the
    rendered API URL matches the stored ID exactly.

  * subscription: keep Auto-Assign row selection independent from the per-row
    key picker. Clicking the dropdown no longer toggles the row's selection,
    and clearing the dropdown no longer snaps the value back to the top-most
    key.

  * subscription: always allow Check when a node is selected. The previous
    gate on "no subscription installed" prevented refreshing a cached status
    that may have become stale after a key was added directly on the remote.

  * guests: extend the filter on the cross-remote guest list with
    field-qualified terms (tag:, remote:, node:, status:, type:) that are
    ANDed across whitespace-separated terms, e.g. "tag:prod remote:cluster1"
    matches guests tagged prod on the cluster1 remote.  Bare words still match
    across all visible columns.

  * guests: make the CPU Usage and Memory Usage columns sortable in the tree
    view; normalize the column label to "Memory Usage" so it matches the rest
    of the UI.

  * guests: promote the cross-remote guest panel to the top-level navigation.

  * migration: indicate the guest's current node in the target-node selector
    (greyed out and labelled "current") so users do not pick a no-op target;
    also add a CPU Usage column next to the existing Memory Usage column so a
    target can be picked by full live utilization.

  * certificates: lay out the certificate-detail KVGrid to fit and wrap long
    values; in the certificate re-check dialog hoist the verification guidance
    and summarize the fleet's certificate issuer.

  * access control: use the plural form for the API Tokens tab name.

  * auto-installer: seed the network and FQDN settings from the saved config
    when editing a prepared answer, so a static configuration is no longer
    reset to DHCP on edit; also accept MiniJinja template expressions in the
    address fields.

  * auto-installer: clear the template counters when the list is emptied on
    edit, and reject duplicate template-counter names instead of silently
    collapsing them into one entry.

  * auto-installer: add a refresh button to the authentication tokens panel.

  * ceph: force a fresh status fetch on a manual dashboard reload instead of
    serving the cached value; the background poll keeps using the cache.

  * subscription: clarify the status labels so the dashboard (remotes),
    the configuration panel (the PDM host's own subscription) and the
    remotes-list column (subscription level) no longer read as contradicting
    each other.

